tinyld
======

tinyld is a small collection of ELF-only tools forked from tcc:
a static linker, standalone assemblers, and a static archive tool.
The goal is to keep the object, archive, and ELF linking code small enough
to use with other small compilers.

Current scope:

- ELF executable output only
- static linking only
- relocatable object input
- static archive input
- a small GNU ld-script subset for INPUT(...) and GROUP(...)
- x86_64, AArch64, and RISC-V 64-bit Linux targets
- standalone assembler output as ELF relocatable `.o` files

Build:

    make

Tools:

- `tinyld`: alias for the x86_64 ELF static linker
- `tinyld-x86_64`: x86_64 ELF static linker
- `tinyld-aarch64`: AArch64 ELF static linker
- `tinyld-riscv64`: RISC-V 64-bit ELF static linker
- `tinyas`: alias for the x86_64 ELF assembler
- `tinyas-x86_64`: x86_64 ELF assembler
- `tinyas-aarch64`: AArch64 ELF assembler
- `tinyas-riscv64`: RISC-V 64-bit ELF assembler
- `tinyar`: small static archive creator/list/extractor for ELF64 `.o` files

Example:

    ./tinyld -static -nostdlib -L/path/to/musl/lib \
        -o hello \
        /path/to/musl/lib/crt1.o \
        /path/to/musl/lib/crti.o \
        hello.o \
        -lc \
        /path/to/musl/lib/crtn.o

Archive example:

    ./tinyar crs libhello.a hello.o helper.o
    ./tinyld -static -nostdlib -L. -L/path/to/musl/lib \
        -o hello \
        /path/to/musl/lib/crt1.o \
        /path/to/musl/lib/crti.o \
        main.o \
        -lhello \
        -lc \
        /path/to/musl/lib/crtn.o

Assembler example:

    ./tinyas-x86_64 -o start.o start.s
    ./tinyld-x86_64 -static -nostdlib -o start start.o

Unsupported by design:

- dynamic libraries
- shared object output
- PIE output
- in-memory execution
- tcc runtime support libraries
